            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I tested this on other terminal (gnome-terminal) and the issue was gone. So I tried changing the `$TERM` environmental variable from \"xterm-256color\" to \"wezterm\" by following instructions from https://wezterm.org/config/lua/config/term.html and it seems that the problem is gone. Note that I had to [install wezterm terminfo](https://wezterm.org/config/lua/config/term.html). Maybe somebody will find this useful.\n\nNow, I'm not really sure if this issue is actually a bug or it is expected behaviour when using wezterm with TERM=xterm-256color, so I'm leaving this issue open for somebody with better understanding to decide.",
