            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Hi folks, just sharing my investigation into this issue:\nThis is a small bug in wezterm, already fixed in [PR #5871](https://github.com/wezterm/wezterm/pull/5871) and is available in the nightly build.\n\n* Repro with `TERM=xterm-256color`: since `xterm-256color` supports the `smglr` capability (i.e. `tui->can_set_lr_margin`), nvim sets the scroll region normally, which then exposes the bug in wezterm.\n* No issue with `TERM=wezterm`: since `wezterm` doesn't support `smglr`, nvim doesn't set the scroll region and falls back to redrawing the region later.\n\n<img width=\"800\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/44bccd43-ed82-432d-a925-dd1633d26642\" />\n\nRelevant code:\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/4edeaaa6e2c1454a6e2ceeca515727954333c2a6/src/nvim/tui/tui.c#L1437-L1448\n\nBTW, issue #34120 already discussed the same problem, and it matches my investigation above. :)",
